                        <div class="faq-answer">The FDA considers 400 mg of caffeine per day safe for most healthy adults. That's roughly four 8-oz cups of brewed coffee. Pregnant women are advised to limit intake to 200 mg per day. Individual tolerance varies based on genetics, body weight, and sensitivity.</div>
