                        <div class="faq-answer">Caffeine has a half-life of about 5 to 6 hours, meaning half the caffeine is still in your system after that time. It takes roughly 10-12 hours for caffeine to be fully eliminated. For example, 200 mg at noon would leave about 100 mg at 5-6 PM and 50 mg at 10-11 PM.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
