                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer">Most sleep experts recommend stopping caffeine at least 6-8 hours before your planned bedtime. Research shows that caffeine consumed even 6 hours before bed can reduce total sleep time by over an hour. If you go to bed at 10 PM, your last caffeinated drink should be before 2-4 PM.</div>
