                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer">No. Caffeine metabolism varies significantly between individuals due to genetics (CYP1A2 gene), body weight, age, medications, and tolerance. Fast metabolizers break down caffeine quickly and may feel little effect, while slow metabolizers can feel jittery from a single cup of coffee.</div>
